I researched how one-way mirror film works and how to apply it to acrylic.  I watched some tutorials showing the wet-application method which involves spraying the acrylic and the film with water and then pressing it on carefully. Bubbles form very easily if rushed, but can be squeezed out using something flat like a credit card. I also compared different film brands, thicknesses, and suppliers, to see which one would give me the best reflective effect.

